-- Australian Miners to Push for Tax Changes, Financial Review Says
-- B y   E l i s a b e t h   B e h r m a n n
-- 2010-10-06T20:20:18Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-10-06/australian-miners-to-push-for-tax-changes-financial-review-says.html
Australian mining companies will seek
changes to the government’s planned profits tax, including
lifting the threshold and making infrastructure spending
deductible, the Australian Financial Review reported, citing
Simon Bennison, chief executive of the Association of Mining and
Exploration Companies. Co-chair of the government’s policy
transition group Don Argus and Resources Minister Martin
Ferguson will hold a policy meeting in Perth today, the Review
said.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Elisabeth Behrmann in Sydney at 
